wikipedia_page.main: Lieutenant Pruett Mullens Dennett (21 January 1899 – 2 June 1918) was a World War I British flying ace.  He was credited with ten aerial victories, the last occurring on the day he was killed in combat.

response: Pruett Mullens Dennett, World War I British flying ace credited with ten aerial victories, is one of those commemorated on the monument.
